1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,962
(Matthew 5:6): 'Blessed are those who hunger and thirst for righteousness.

2
00:00:05,912 --> 00:00:16,675
Jesus went up a mountain to a valley, into a field, and power went out of him preaching to the multitude: ‘Blessed are they which do hunger and thirst after righteousness for they shall be filled.

3
00:00:16,675 --> 00:00:19,725
Methinks this text is apt to my discourse.

4
00:00:19,725 --> 00:00:26,800
Blessed are they that hunger for righteousness and endure work and poverty here, for this is but a moment and will surely pass.

5
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:29,375
They are blessed though not most blessed.

6
00:00:29,375 --> 00:00:36,837
Blessed are they that hunger not to be deprived of God, albeit the wonder is that man can be without him without whom he cannot be.

7
00:00:36,837 --> 00:00:42,887
St Augustine says it is amazing that anyone should live apart from him apart from whom he cannot.

8
00:00:42,887 --> 00:00:44,125
live at all.

9
00:00:44,125 --> 00:00:46,962
They are blessed and yet not most blessed.

10
00:00:46,962 --> 00:00:54,075
More blessed those who so hunger that they cannot live without God; that is a fiery affection which transforms their nature.

11
00:00:54,075 --> 00:01:01,325
The while a man yet finds in his desire or in his hope or his affection anything impermanent, he is not most blessed.

12
00:01:01,325 --> 00:01:03,950
He is blessed but not most blessed.

13
00:01:03,950 --> 00:01:16,812
Blessed, supremely blessed, are they who are installed in the eternal now, transcending time and place and form and matter; unmoved by weal or woe or wealth or want, for in so far as things are motionless they are like eternity.

14
00:01:16,812 --> 00:01:22,625
The heaven adjoining the eternal now, wherein the angels are, is motionless, immoveable.

15
00:01:22,625 --> 00:01:34,900
But the heaven next to that which touches the eternal now, wherein the angels are, and betwixt (that and) the heaven where the sun is, is set in motion by angelic force, revolving once in every hundred years.

16
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:39,900
The heaven the sun is in, moved by angelic force, goes round once a year.

17
00:01:39,900 --> 00:01:45,537
The heaven the moon is in, again, is driven by angelic force and goes round once a month.

18
00:01:45,537 --> 00:01:52,550
The nearer the eternal now the more immoveable they are, and the further off and more unlike to the eternal now the easier to move.

19
00:01:52,550 --> 00:02:07,350
The heaven of the sun and moon and stars is moved by the impulse of their angel, so that they are spinning in this temporal now; and the eternal now imparts their motion, that being so energetic that from the motion the eternal now imparts, all things derive their life and being.

20
00:02:07,350 --> 00:02:14,462
Now the lowest powers of the soul are nobler than the highest part of heaven, where it adjoins the angels and the eternal now.

21
00:02:14,462 --> 00:02:26,275
Moreover, all things get their life and being from the motion there imparted by the eternal now; and if that is so noble, then what would ye expect where the soul in her superior powers contacts the ground of God?

22
00:02:26,275 --> 00:02:33,875
How exalted, think ye, that must be?—Follow then after this now, and reach this now and possess this eternal now.

23
00:02:33,875 --> 00:02:38,075
May we stand next the eternal now and so be in possession of it.

24
00:02:38,075 --> 00:02:40,412
So help us O divine power.

25
00:02:40,412 --> 00:02:52,812
One master says: Grace springs from the heart of the Father and flows into his Son and in the oneness of them twain it proceeds from the Wisdom of the Son into the Gift of the Holy Ghost and in the Holy Ghost is sent into the soul.

26
00:02:52,812 --> 00:03:00,612
Grace is the face of God which is clearly stamped in the soul without any means by the Spirit of God, giving the soul the form of God.

27
00:03:00,612 --> 00:03:04,712
St Dionysius says: The angels are the divine mind.

28
00:03:04,712 --> 00:03:13,750
Moreover St Paul declares concerning those who live the angelic life here in the flesh, that into them there flows the mind of God as it does into the angels.

29
00:03:13,750 --> 00:03:19,625
He also says the intellectual light, God namely, has given likeness to the rational soul.

30
00:03:19,625 --> 00:03:25,387
Quoth St Paul: He who cleaves unto God with his whole being becomes one spirit with God.

31
00:03:25,387 --> 00:03:27,025
So help us God.

32
00:03:27,025 --> 00:03:27,975
Amen.
